### Residual Risks in the Fixed Code

The corrected code addresses all Tier 1 and Tier 2 issues but intentionally leaves certain Tier 3 concerns for the team to address based on deployment context:

| Residual Risk | Why It's Not Fixed Here | Recommended Solution |
|---|---|---|
| No CSRF protection | Requires architectural decision (session-based vs. token-based auth model) | `Flask-WTF` CSRFProtect for session-based; not needed for pure API with Bearer tokens |
| No security headers | Depends on deployment (reverse proxy may handle this)
